news.title: China's security agency in Hong Kong buys $65 million luxury villa
news.para: The 666-square metre (7,171-square foot) mansion has five bedrooms, three car parking spaces, a garden, its own lift and is described by its developer as "a residential jewel that secures panoramic views, low density and luxuriant living".

news.title: Chinese property stocks soar on fresh regulatory support
news.para: CIFI Holdings (Group) Co Ltd soared 40% while Country Garden Holdings Co Ltd surged 23%. The Hang Seng Mainland Properties Index rose 8%.

news.title: Bank of Maharashtra raises one-year MCLR by 10 bps
news.para: The benchmark one-year MCLR, used to price most of consumer loans such as auto, personal and home, has been revised upwards to 7.90 per cent from 7.80 per cent, the lender said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Godrej Properties' net profit up 87.60% in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income stood at Rs 369.20 crore in Q2 FY23, a growth of 10.47 per cent from Rs 334.22 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Uttarakhand: Only 14 of 195 brick kilns in Haridwar 'run with permits'
news.para: The air quality index (AQI) was at 165 on Tuesday. Environmentalists said that despite the Ganga flowing through the district, the poor air quality shows that various other factors are adding to the air pollution in the district.

news.title: Mumbai: Consumer forum directs probe against Khar housing society
news.para: The complainant housing society had moved the commission in 2012 seeking several reliefs, including demarcation with boundary walls between the two buildings, possession of the society office and parking spaces.

news.title: Residents of other Chintels Paradiso towers demand authorities to expedite audit
news.para: Now, residents of towers G and H have complained that there are several structural defects in these two towers, such as visible cracks in balconies and seepage.

news.title: On-book portfolio of HFCs is expected to grow by 10-12% in FY23: ICRA
news.para: The gross non-performing assets (GNPAs) declined by 6 bps to 3.1% as on June 30, 2022, from 3.2% as on March 31, 2022, due to increase in the on-book portfolio and recovery in the non-housing segment of some large HFCs.

news.title: Tier-II cities emerging as real estate growth engines: Magicbricks Report
news.para: Magicbricks.com is owned by Magicbricks Realty Services, which is a subsidiary of Times Internet.

news.title: Phoenix Mills' posts net profit of Rs 221.89 crore in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income stood at Rs 683.49 crore in Q2 FY23, a growth of 80.03 per cent from Rs 379.66 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Aptus Value Housing Finance's net profit up 44.63% in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income stood at Rs 277.05 crore in Q2 FY23, a growth of 36.32 per cent from Rs 203.23 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Birla Corporation posts Rs 56 crore loss in Q2 FY23
news.para: ​Revenue of the company increased 19.3 per cent at Rs 2042 crore during the second quarter as compared to Rs 1711 crore in the previous similar period, a statement by the primarily cement manufacturing firm said on Tuesday.

news.title: HDFC Capital Advisors invests over Rs 1,550 crore in six projects of SP Real Estate
news.para: The investment made through structured debt instruments will flow into six projects spread over nearly 7 million square feet in Mumbai and Pune. It will be utilised for financial closure of projects, repayment of high-cost debt, and working capital, the companies said.

news.title: Greenply Industries' net profit down 26% to Rs 23.6 crore in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company for the quarter under review posted a revenue of Rs Rs 494.7 crore from operations, a 14 per cent jump over the corresponding period revenue of Rs 432.4 crore.

news.title: Keystone Realtors' Rs 635 crore-IPO to open on November 14
news.para: According to the Red Herring Prospectus (RHP), the Mumbai-based company now plans to raise Rs 635 crore. The size of the IPO has been reduced from Rs 850 crore earlier.
